			<b>09 Sep 2010</b>
			 &mdash; <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100914063926/http://www.eu-russiacentre.org/tag/uk" rel="tag">UK</a>					</span>
		<p>Prime Minister Vladimir Putin’s possible return to the presidency should not be welcomed. The publication notes that privately, some western governments are indicating they would view it as a retrograde step.<span id="more-16723"></span> President Dmitry Medvedev has launched a program to modernise and diversify Russia’s economy, reducing its reliance on resources. Real modernisation would also entail reform and democratisation of Russia’s system of governance. Putin has given no impression that he thinks such modernisation is needed, or that he wants to lead it.</p>
<span class="Source">Source: <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100914063926/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/ee1977c4-bb7e-11df-a136-00144feab49a.html" target="_blank">The Financial Times </a></span>	
